  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STRENGTHENING THE PRODUCTION BASE OF THE AMAZON PAPER: Farmers, Artisans, papermakers, carpenters and potters.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Associa&#xE7;&#xE3;o Amazon Paper (AP), $344,000 over three years AP will develop and consolidate a production chain to benefit small- scale farmers, artists, craftspeople and the urban unemployed in Par&#xE1; - including African descendants, youths and women, by creating jobs - improving their income and strengthening the five organizations to which they belong. AP will produce and sell paper and paper crafts made by combining Japanese papermaking techniques with traditional Amazon fiber- and dye-processing - which will also promote the biodiversity and the sustainable use of natural resources in the Amazon region.</narrative>
  </description>
